sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: ColiAlert
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: It is formed by biobricks already available in the registry.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This biobrick makes E. coli to have pink color under natural conditions. It is formed by biobricks already available in the registry. It is responsible for the production of yellow chromoprotein (BBa_K1033910) which in the presence of basic media change their color to pink. This part can be used as a reporter cell lysis.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The endoglucanase gene was added to biobrick wrongly. The biobrick works and should be made ​​without this gene.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Deborah M Landim Zanforlin

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0015
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Double terminator consisting of BBa_B0010 and BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: fwYellow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This chromoprotein naturally exhibits strong color when expressed.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This construct is synthetic. It was synthesized from a template where the consensus sequence for the "color dependancy" in order to obtain a chromoprotein with a unique yellow color.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Sabri Jamal

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K914003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Amplification of the plasmid pJOE3075 (Dr. Altenbuchner).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: L-rhamnose-inducible promoter is capable of high-level recombinant protein expression in the presence of L-rhamnose, it is also tightly regulated in the absence of L-rhamnose by the addition of D-glucose.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: One base pair modified (90: A -> T) to avoid EcoRI site. Mutation made in a less conserved base pair.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Denis Samuylov

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K523008
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a modified version of <partinfo>BBa_K265008</partinfo> for use with the BioSandwich protocol of Edinburgh 2011.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Mun Ching Lee, Sylvia Ispasanie

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I746361
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The source of the DNA is the P2 phage genome.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the PO promoter taken from the P2 phage genome. It is an inducible promoter that is activated by a class of activators, including P2 ogr (I746350), PSP3 pag (I746351) and phiR73 delta (I746352). These different activators should cause different levels of activity of the PO promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Stefan Milde

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg
